<p itemprop="description">Network architecture involves designing and implementing the structure and organization of computer networks to support government operations, ensuring security, performance, and reliability.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand network architecture principles and recognise the importance of network design in supporting government IT services.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can contribute to network architecture projects, understand network protocols and topologies, and implement network solutions following established designs.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design comprehensive network architectures, optimize network performance, and ensure network security and compliance with government standards.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead enterprise network architecture strategy, design complex multi-site networks, and establish network standards and best practices across government organizations.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

